      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "CFD solver must be under documented version control with regression test suite demonstrating stable results across patch versions.",
      "rationale": "ANSYS Fluent 2022R2 used under institutional software quality plan. Version-locked simulation environment with documented regression tests for internal flow benchmarks. Change log reviewed; no solver-relevant patches applied mid-study. SQA level 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Solver must reproduce analytical or manufactured solutions for canonical internal flow cases at published accuracy order.",
      "rationale": "Fluent verified against Taylor-Couette and lid-driven cavity benchmarks. Second-order spatial accuracy confirmed via manufactured solution test. Published ASME V&V 20 benchmark results for turbulent pipe flow reproduced within 1.2% of reference. Code verification level 2 satisfied."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Grid convergence index (GCI) must be computed using at least three systematically refined meshes with GCI < 5% for the primary QoI (NIH) at the worst-case operating point.",
      "rationale": "A mesh refinement study was conducted using two mesh densities (4.2M and 8.7M elements). The coarse-to-medium refinement ratio is 1.38, which is within the recommended range. NIH values at the nominal operating point (3500 RPM, 5 L/min) showed a 3.1% change between mesh levels, and the team concluded that discretization error was adequately controlled. However, a formal three-mesh Richardson extrapolation with GCI computation was not completed, and the finest mesh required by the acceptance criterion was not generated due to computational resource constraints. The achieved level is therefore 1, falling below the required level of 2 for this factor at MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental boundary conditions must be documented with uncertainty bounds and matched to simulation inputs within stated tolerances.",
      "rationale": "In vitro test rig operated with bovine blood analog (glycerol-water, matched hematocrit 35%). Flow rates set by calibrated Coriolis meter (±0.5% FS). Inlet pressure measured by flush-mounted transducer (±0.3 mmHg). All boundary conditions transferred to CFD with documented uncertainty mapping. Test conditions level 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric (e.g., E% or validation uncertainty) must be reported for primary QoI against experimental data.",
      "rationale": "NIH compared at all 5 operating points using relative error metric E% = (CFD − Exp)/Exp × 100. Mean E% = 14.2%, max E% = 21.7% at 4500 RPM/7 L/min. Validation uncertainty U_val computed per ASME V&V 20 framework incorporating experimental uncertainty, numerical uncertainty, and input uncertainty. All comparisons documented in validation report VR-CPB-2024-03. Output comparison level 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs used in validation must be directly traceable to the clinical decision QoI (relative hemolysis index RH).",
      "rationale": "NIH selected as primary validation QoI; directly related to RH via published power-law hemolysis model (Giersiepen-Wurzinger). Shear stress exposure time integral computed from particle tracking along 5000 streamlines per operating point. Traceability matrix linking NIH to RH documented in credibility plan CP-CPB-2024-01. Relevance of QoI level 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation activities must be conducted on the same device geometry and within the operating envelope of the COU.",
      "rationale": "Validation performed on the FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry, which is the same geometry used in the COU tolerance sensitivity study. Operating points span the full clinical range (2–7 L/min, 3000–4500 RPM). Blood analog fluid properties matched to clinical hematocrit range. Validation activities directly relevant to COU; level 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative convergence must be demonstrated with residuals below 1e-5 for all transport equations and monitored QoI showing < 0.5% variation over final 500 iterations.",
      "rationale": "All simulations run to steady-state with continuity residual < 1e-6, momentum < 1e-5, turbulence quantities < 1e-5. NIH monitor showed < 0.2% variation over final 1000 iterations at all operating points. Solver error level 1 achieved and meets required level."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Simulation setup must be independently reviewed by a second qualified analyst prior to result extraction.",
      "rationale": "Independent peer review of simulation setup conducted by senior analyst not involved in model construction. Boundary condition assignments, turbulence model selection (SST k-ω), and hemolysis model constants verified against published sources. No setup errors identified. Use error level 1 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Governing equations and turbulence closure model must be appropriate for the flow regime and documented with justification.",
      "rationale": "Reynolds-averaged Navier-Stokes with SST k-ω closure selected based on literature survey of rotary blood pump CFD studies. Non-Newtonian blood rheology modeled via Carreau-Yasuda model with published constants for bovine blood at 35% hematocrit. Model form justification documented in modeling report MR-CPB-2024-01. Level 1 achieved."
    },
    {
